==English==
===Phrasal verb===
''to'' '''[[speak]] [[for]]''' ''[[oneself]]''

# To [[provide]] an [[opinion]] [[only]] on one's own [[behalf]].
#:''I'm here '''speaking for myself''', not for my company.''
# To give an [[opinion]] with which others do not necessarily [[agree]].
#:'''''Speak for yourself'''!  I think it's a great idea.''

===Usage note===
* In the imperative especially, this term has a context of "I don't agree" or "believe what you like".

